        <p class="message">Over the years, we've worked with a lot of property owners on recertifications and the ones who waited always ended up paying more.</p>
        
        <p class="message">Not because the inspection itself gets more expensive, but because once the city gets involved first, it's never just the inspection anymore. It's fines, emergency timelines, re-inspections, and sometimes construction work just to get back into compliance. One owner we worked with ended up spending close to three times what a routine recertification would have cost simply because the clock ran out.</p>
        
        <p class="message">Getting ahead of it for {{Property Address}} — while there's still runway is almost always the cheaper, calmer path.</p>
        
